As the creative powerhouse behind hugely influential band The Kinks, Ray Davies was responsible 
for writing some of the best-loved songs of the 60s, including pop classics You Really Got Me, 
Tired of Waiting For You, Dedicated Follower of Fashion, Sunny Afternoon and Waterloo Sunset. 
Alan Yentob meets Davies, a unique talent who describes with rare candour his troubled relationship 
with fame and the vicissitudes of his career. They also discuss a new album of Klassic Kinks 
Kollaborations which is near completion and features musical luminaries such as Bruce Springsteen, 
Mumford and Sons and Metallica.
